  "prompt": "How early can you check in at the airport for international flight?",
  "response": "The check-in time for international flights can vary depending on the airline and the airport's policies. Generally, most airlines open their check-in counters 3 hours before the scheduled departure time for international flights. However, some airlines might allow check-in as early as 24 hours in advance. \n\nIt's always a good idea to check with your specific airline for their check-in policy and to arrive early enough to complete the check-in process, drop off your luggage, and go through security and immigration before your flight.",
